        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2066461965" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16055308020451177053">c2004: FWFTB: 1936, RAF, pacifist, compassion, peace. So, Locus said that this was &apos;one of the finest SF novels of 2002 and the Independent said that Mr Priest had concocted &apos;an impressive set of imagined places and times&apos;. All of which I may have agreed to if I had only understood all the nuances. It entranced me to the end - but did I actually understand any of it? Not a whit which is why I am unable to recommend to the normal crew. <i>&quot;We were too far apart to speak to each other,but it was cert</i></span>
  <span id="freeText16055308020451177053" style="display:none">c2004: FWFTB: 1936, RAF, pacifist, compassion, peace. So, Locus said that this was 'one of the finest SF novels of 2002 and the Independent said that Mr Priest had concocted 'an impressive set of imagined places and times'. All of which I may have agreed to if I had only understood all the nuances. It entranced me to the end - but did I actually understand any of it? Not a whit which is why I am unable to recommend to the normal crew. <i>"We were too far apart to speak to each other,but it was certainly him and because he was looking around our eyes briefly met. I raised my hand in greeting. He made no response and walked on."</i></span>
