<div id="review_3054792695" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3054792695" />
    <a title="Larry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8902279-larry"><img alt="Larry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1334880316p2/8902279.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3054792695?book_show_action=true">Dec 01, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Larry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Larry" href="/user/show/8902279-larry">Larry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3054792695" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer597523653117976710">This is an amazing book. Be warned, there are multiple, intersecting timelines. The story is told from multiple points of view, not in linear sequence. There are twins, body doubles, multiple versions of the same character. Both main characters have traumatic injuries that impair their mental processes, so it is unclear whether some events actually happen or are delusions. <br/><br/>Never-the-less, the book is tightly constructed. Priest is a master of nuance and detail. The ending is ambiguous, but I bel</span>
  <span id="freeText597523653117976710" style="display:none">This is an amazing book. Be warned, there are multiple, intersecting timelines. The story is told from multiple points of view, not in linear sequence. There are twins, body doubles, multiple versions of the same character. Both main characters have traumatic injuries that impair their mental processes, so it is unclear whether some events actually happen or are delusions. <br /><br />Never-the-less, the book is tightly constructed. Priest is a master of nuance and detail. The ending is ambiguous, but I believe that was delineate. It is challenging--not an easy read--but well worth the effort. </span>
  <a data-text-id="597523653117976710" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


